Q.14 --> What is the use of a span tag? Explain with example?

Ans:-
      
      HTML <span> tag is used as a generic container of inline elements. It is used for styling purpose or to add attributes to a section of text without creating a new line of content. 

      Example: 
               Add Text Color using <span> Tag:
               <p> color: <span style="color: orange;">orange <span style="color: white;"> white</span> <span style="color: green;"> green</span></p>

               Add Text Color and Background Color using <span> Tag:
               <p> color: <span style="color: white; background-color: red;">WNR</span> <span style="color: blue; background-color: gray;"> BNG</span> <span style="color: coral; background-color: aqua;"> CNA</span></p>

  
